  "prompt": "Once I've installed Windows 10, if I have to factory reset my laptop, will it revert to Windows 8.1 or stay on Windows 10?",
  "response": "If you've installed Windows 10 on a laptop that originally came with Windows 8.1 and then you perform a factory reset, the outcome depends on how the factory reset is configured by the manufacturer.\n\n1. **Manufacturer's Recovery Partition**: If your laptop has a recovery partition created by the manufacturer, performing a factory reset will likely restore the laptop to its original factory state, which means it will revert back to Windows 8.1.\n\n2. **Windows 10 Installation**: If you have performed a clean installation of Windows 10 (and overwritten the recovery partition), then a factory reset may simply reinstall Windows 10.\n\nTo summarize, if you reset your laptop using the built-in recovery option and that option is set to restore to the original factory settings, it will go back to Windows 8.1. If you are using a reset method that reinstalls Windows 10 (like from a USB or through the recovery options for Windows 10), it will stay on Windows 10. \n\nTo check the recovery options available on your laptop, you can go into the Recovery settings in Windows 10 by navigating to **Settings > Update & Security > Recovery**.",
